Still on my Vietnamese food kick this week and my search has brought me to Dong A, a very modest restaurant that looks like it has been there forever.
It turns out to be yet another "gem in a rundown strip mall.
" You definitely won't come here for the ambiance, but your taste buds will thank you!
I find the flavors here to be a bit bolder than in the other Vietnamese restaurants I've tried; this doesn't make them necessarily better than the others, just different - and in a good way.
Good food, low prices, friendly service, and close to where I live ... glad I found this place!

